00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,840
The work here isn't easier

321
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:54,160
than when you were in the military.

322
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:55,800
Could your legs

323
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:56,840
stand it?

324
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:58,480
I'm fine.

325
00:17:58,600 --> 00:17:59,600
I've recovered well.

326
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,680
I have no problems with walking,

327
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,800
running, or jumping.

328
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:04,680
But when it's cloudy or rainy,

329
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,040
I always feel

330
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:07,160
bloating and pain.

331
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,160
Didn't you go to the hospital?

332
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,280
Yeah, I went to
the Military Region Hospital.

333
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:14,440
The doctor said the steel screws
they put in my leg

334
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,680
had deformed.

335
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:17,800
They couldn't take them out.

336
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:19,600
I have to endure it.

337
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,600
Now they use

338
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,800
titanium screws in surgeries.

339
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:25,920
If we had such screws at that time,

340
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:28,800
my leg might

341
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,640
fully recover.

342
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,920
I may not be demobilized.

